textBeforeTable: 2015 Tour Dates Low price $16 High price $146 Average Price $63 Past 12 Months Find Tickets Ratking Ticket Prices If you're looking for the future of New York sound, you'll find it walking the urban edge of this group that is not so much up-and-coming. Ratking has fully arrived. Where else will you look to the labeled 'New York music' scene and find such a mix of alt rock, drum and bass, jazz and even reggae? Combined with their sped up vocal samples mashed up with other stray sounds, there's nothing that can touch the soundscape that is Ratking. From the electric piano and saxophone on "Snow Beach" to the horn riff on "One In a Million," the tracks that combine to make up "So It Goes" solidify the opinion many have had of Ratking for quite some time. The trio of Wiki (aka Patrick Morales), Hak (Hakeem Lewis) and Sporting Life (Eric Adiele) have a catalog of hits under their belt that has set them apart from others on the New York hip-hop scene.
